summary: Completed comprehensive testing of Prompt Manager MVP. All backend APIs working correctly. Frontend setup page and navigation protection working as expected. All 4 default templates properly seeded and accessible via API.
passed_tests: Backend health check (/api/health) - returns 200 with status and timestamp
Backend root endpoint (/api/) - returns message and version
Settings API (/api/settings) - returns unconfigured state initially with is_configured: false
Templates API (/api/templates) - returns exactly 4 default templates: Agent Persona, Task Executor, Knowledge Expert, Minimal Prompt
API Keys CRUD - POST /api/keys creates new key with proper structure
API Keys CRUD - GET /api/keys lists all keys correctly
API Keys CRUD - DELETE /api/keys/{id} removes key successfully
Frontend setup page loads at /setup with correct header and form fields
Frontend redirects to /setup when GitHub not configured (navigation protection)
Frontend form validation prevents submission with empty fields
Frontend displays GitHub connection form with token, owner, repo fields
Frontend shows backend validation errors for invalid GitHub credentials
All interactive elements have proper data-testid attributes for testing
